OL,3,CParents raise concern as island school
OL,4,Cclasses become 'too full'
OL,6,FParent, Suzanne Pontin said: "There
OL,7,Fhave been concerns with class sizes -
OL,8,Fparticularly with La Mare and Les
OL,9,FVarendes - when you've got the 2
OL,10,Fschools merging and obviously more
OL,11,Fchildren which means bigger classes.
OL,13,F"You are not really sure how the
OL,14,Fteacher ratio is going to be split
OL,15,Fwhen you've got the 2 schools merging."
OL,17,FStates of Guernsey believe that large
OL,18,Fclasses don't affect their students'
OL,19,Facademic achievement and have
OL,20,Fsuggested some large classes are
OL,21,Factually outperforming smaller ones.
